  "description": "¶AI Agents for Formal Mathematics: External Landscape Survey Survey of external tools, research, and practices for LLM agents doing formal mathematics with proof assistants. Focused on what exists outside this repository that could improve agent mathematical capability here.\n¶1. LLM-Based Mathematical Reasoning Agents ¶DeepSeek-Prover-V2 (DeepSeek, 2025) Formal theorem proving in Lean 4. Key innovation: subgoal decomposition — the model writes an informal proof sketch first, decomposes into formal subgoals, then proves each subgoal. Trained with GRPO (not PPO) reinforcement learning. Achieved 88.9% on MiniF2F-test, 49 out of 658 problems on FormalMATH. Open-weight (7B and 671B MoE variants).\n",
  "keywords": "formalization, proof-assistants, ai-agents",
  "name": "Survey: AI Agents for Formal Mathematics (External Landscape, 2026)",
